WEBVTT

00:10:29.209 --> 00:10:32.005
enablers to allies.

00:10:32.499 --> 00:10:33.855
Number two:

00:10:33.879 --> 00:10:35.294
change the laws.

00:10:37.029 --> 00:10:38.467
How many of you out there know

00:10:38.491 --> 00:10:40.910
whether or not you have
a forced arbitration clause

00:10:40.934 --> 00:10:42.832
in your employment contract?

00:10:44.095 --> 00:10:45.245
Not a lot of hands.

00:10:45.269 --> 00:10:46.997
And if you don't know, you should,

00:10:47.021 --> 00:10:48.251
and here's why.

00:10:49.096 --> 00:10:50.352
TIME Magazine calls it,

00:10:50.376 --> 00:10:52.015
right there on the screen,

00:10:52.039 --> 00:10:55.394
"The teeny tiny little print in contracts

00:10:55.418 --> 00:10:58.801
that keeps sexual
harassment claims unheard."

00:10:59.646 --> 00:11:01.015
Here's what it is.